Package ca.uwo.csteam14

Class POI

java.lang.Object
ca.uwo.csteam14.POI
public class POI extends Object
POI entity used for storing information about a POI such as the name, coordinates, category, etc.

A POI is created with the constructor, and the other attributes are set using setters. POIs can be compared for equality using the isEqualTo method.

Example Use: 
 
     POI p = new POI(40001);
     p.setName("The Grad Club");
     p.setBuilding("Middlesex College");
     p.setFloor("0");
Example Output: No output, but a POI object is created with the given ID, name, building, and floor.
Since:
2023-03-07
Version:
1.0.0
Author:
Daniel Gomes, Robert Beemer
